==English==
===Pronunciation===
{{rfap}}
===Etymology===
From the [[w:Yiddish language|Yiddish]] (''yarmlke''), from the [[w:Polish language|Polish]] ''[[jarmułka]]'' and the [[w:Ukrainean language|Ukrainean]] (''yarmulka''), ''[[skullcap]].'' This is akin to the [[w:Turkish language|Turkish]] (''yağmurluk''), that is ''[[rainwear]].'' This [[term]] entered English in 1903.

===Noun===
{{en-noun-reg}}

# A skullcap worn by Jewish males, also known as a [[Kippah]].

